e, from illness to gardening. Conversational and evocative, this book calls on us to ask how we might make ourselves more open to experiences of rapturous joy and freedom.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aRapture (Christian eschatology) 0aRapture (Christian eschatology). 0aReligious awakeningxChristianity. 0aSelf. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Movements / Phenomenology.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.7312/hami2015440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780231561686423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780231561686/original  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles